reviews.text:
One of many malls dotting Causeway Bay area. Its lobby has a high vertical clearance. Trendy crowd...maybe because there was an Avengers exhibition going on at the time of my visit.

Had some difficulty finding Marketplace but as it turned out, was called Jasons, which is located two floors below ground.

The building had separate entries for the shopping areas and the office/residential area.
Amazing department store with all that you need in it. Great shops and restaurants
Large shopping mall in central location, not easy or pleasant to walk around or navigate. There are better malls in HK.

The big bookstore alone is worthy for a visit. The food court is decent and the general selection of stores is nicely put together. Directly connected to the mass transit too so this location is hard to beat.

Great shopping mall with can different kind of shops, including fashion, books store, restaurants, and Apple store.
Unlike other shopping mall, their escalator can easily reach each floor.
And there is a sky garden located on 4/F, which is a great place for relaxing, and it's open from 10am to 10pm

result.name: Nadai Unatoto Charcoal Grilled Eel Speciality

reviews.text: The eel rice is okay but not fatty enough, the eel egg roll is overcooked and is very salty.
Always did fancy the aroma of charcoal infused meat! Though I would add that I went around 330pm where there was no crowd at all.

No-frill charcoal-grilled eel restaurant, with rice bowls as simple as just a bowl of white rice with two pieces of grilled eel and grilled eel sauce. Nevertheless, the eel is properly seasoned, fleshy and tender, while the skin is fatty with mild aroma of charcoal. The tables are clean, the restaurant is well-lit, the waiters are polite and helpful. The price is a bit more expensive compared to average grilled eel rice but the quality of the eel is higher as well.

All japanese eel.  They grill it themselves and they don’t serve anything else.

Quality is quite good.

Japanese eel rice freshly grilled on Bincho charcoal. This place is for people who like the real eel rice experience in Japan as they only have eel rice (around HK$100 for one person portion, around HK$200 for two person portion) and some veggies sides for extra cost on the menu. Rare to find well made eel rice in Hong Kong which is not just microwaved. Still, the eel's skin could be grilled crispier and remember to add the seasoning on the table. The seven spices was good as it had black sesame mixed in.

reviews.text:
本当に美味しいうなぎを香港周辺で食べるのなら、シンセンの「坂田」がおすすめですが、坂田に行くのは時間がかかります。
ここならばお手軽に香港でうなぎが食べられるので、満足度は高いです。値段もリーズナブルで、肝吸いや、う巻きなどのサイドメニューも充実しています。
超好食呀，任加飯已經令我心心眼啦😍😍
The eel rice is okay but not fatty enough, the eel egg roll is overcooked and is very salty.
Always did fancy the aroma of charcoal infused meat! Though I would add that I went around 330pm where there was no crowd at all.

No-frill charcoal-grilled eel restaurant, with rice bowls as simple as just a bowl of white rice with two pieces of grilled eel and grilled eel sauce. Nevertheless, the eel is properly seasoned, fleshy and tender, while the skin is fatty with mild aroma of charcoal. The tables are clean, the restaurant is well-lit, the waiters are polite and helpful. The price is a bit more expensive compared to average grilled eel rice but the quality of the eel is higher as well.
